body:
have you looked at these docs:
https://www.onnxruntime.ai/docs/reference/execution-providers/OpenVINO-ExecutionProvider.html#cc-api
@MaajidKhan  , do you think you can help provide a better example for the user? Thanks.

@ledaiduongvnth 
First way, you can leverage OpenVINO Execution provider and it's options is by using the **onnxruntime_perf_test** tool which comes built in when you build onnxruntime with OpenVINO. (As george mentioned at the top)

secondly, you can checkout my blog.
https://nmaajidkhan.medium.com/onnx-runtime-openvino-c-inference-e682b075fdaf
This blog talks about a cpp sample and it demonstrates complete end to end inferencing of an image using a squeezenet onnx model using onnxruntime-openvino.

It will also help you understand different runtime options that are available with the API.
code here: https://github.com/MaajidKhan/onnxruntime-openvino-cpp/tree/main/1_ONNXRT_OpenVINO_CPP_sample
@MaajidKhan Thank you for your useful example, it helps me a lot!
